Package org.neo4j.index.internal.gbptree

Class RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.lifecycle.LifecycleAdapter
      • org.neo4j.index.internal.gbptree.RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Lifecycle
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GroupingRecoveryCleanupWorkCollector, RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector.IgnoringRecoveryCleanupWorkCollector, RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector.ImmediateRecoveryCleanupWorkCollector
    public abstract class RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector
extends LifecycleAdapter
    Place to add recovery cleanup work to be done as part of recovery of GBPTree.

    Lifecycle.init() must prepare implementing class to be reused, probably by cleaning current state. After this, implementing class must be ready to receive new jobs through add(CleanupJob).

    Jobs may be processed during add or start.

    Take full responsibility for closing added CleanupJobs as soon as possible after run.
